Horde <BR>PoF - 1, PoA - 1, PoH - 1 <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarkomen42.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOmen42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardaholic</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/10/02 10:22:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumdruid.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid Armor</span><hr size=1> Uh, leather.<br><br>Chest: Foreman's Tunic.<br>Legs: Thurg legs.<br>Arms: ES Arms.<br>Hands: Gnome skins gloves, no small races can wear.<br>Waist: Halloween EK event belt, 5 ac 5 wis 5 sta I think.<br>Wrists: Runed Mithril Bracers.<br>Earring: Ek event earring, 4 wis and some hp/mana and ac.<br>Earring: Earring of Woven Bark. 2 ac 35hp/mana right click snare. Got it in a group.<br>Feet: GEB.<br>Head: Othmir cap.<br>Back: Mammoth hide cloak.<br>Face: 8 str/wis jewel crafted thingy.<br>Neck: Druid/Cleric Tunare only necklace, right click grasping roots. 7 ac 3 wis 2 cha I think.<br>Rings: The +6 wis ones.<br>Primary: Velium Stone Etched Mace.<br>Secondary: Testament of Vanear.<br>Ranged: Small Wisdom Diety.<br>Ammo: Fishing bait(nice to leave on your body while waiting for a res).<br>Shoulders: Heh almost forgot, some 0 ac resist with wis on it shoulders from the same EK event at Halloween. 10 vs cold fire and magic. <p>Harabec Woodwalker<br>Wanderer of 51 Seasons<br>Bears of Oboo</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubeechwoodgrey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beechwoodgrey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/12/02 2:21:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumdruid.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid Armor</span><hr size=1> well..if you are talking absolutely no twinking:<br><br>weapons: 1hs scimtar, 1hb clubs &amp; maces, 2hb staffs &lt;these can  be found on the mob and keep your ears peeled for anyone giving away fs or brass&gt;<br><br>armor: leather, cloth from the mob in the newbie areas &lt;save all the ruined wolf pelts you can so you can make your own armor&gt;<br><br>jewelry: your goal is to reach 200 wis someday, but mana and hp are what counts at a low lev. <br><br>If you are truely going to have a go at this with no tweeking  i congratulate you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  i have alot of respect for someone learning the char from the ground up. <br><br>Oh..almost forgot, bookmark this site <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eqdruids.com">eqdruids.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> the armor chart is great and gives you several options and a heads up on what you will need to upgrade and make a hot key that says &quot;Sorry i don't get sow till lev 14&quot;<br><br>Have fun and goodluck to ya <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>BWG<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarkomen42.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOmen42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardaholic</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/12/02 10:27:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumdruid.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid Armor</span><hr size=1> Twinking casters really doesn't do a lot. <p>Harabec Woodwalker<br>Wanderer of 51 Seasons<br>Bears of Oboo</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubeechwoodgrey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beechwoodgrey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/12/02 3:54:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumdruid.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid Armor</span><hr size=1> erm.. imho twinking makes a hell of a diff. caster or melee, that's the reason why so many ppl that are able to do it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>here's a few items i use to twink with<br><br>velium wedding rings     2 * 6ac 65hp<br>blk sapp neck              65hp 65 mana<br>&quot;    &quot;      ears              2* 25hp 35mana<br>plat dragon totem        30hp 50 mana<br>embroaided blk sleeves 10hp 25 mana<br>crystaline silk belt        20hp 20 mana 3wis/int<br>sarnak battle shield      40hp 25 ac 5str/sta<br>frozen orb                   40mana 2ac 3wis/int<br><br>as you can see the mana alone &lt;not counting the +wis items&gt; is 270 which is equal to a lev 17 with 70 wis.<br><br>hp items add to 345 hp<br><br>as far as arcane skills &lt;abj, alt, conj,..etc.&gt; go, twinking makes little diff..you still have to bring them up if you want to avoid fizzles major twink or naked newbie.<br><br>also..very few twinks have to run their asses off collecting bones chips, bat wings, belts, webs, pelts..etc to buy their next lev of spells.. so once again i applaud any high lev that is determined not to twink, it's a hell of a temptation.<br><br>BWG &lt;twinkaholic&gt;<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarkomen42.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOmen42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardaholic</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/12/02 4:17:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumdruid.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid Armor</span><hr size=1> To my knowledge +mana items don't give full mana until higher levels. Being about 20 or so, I'm not sure exactly what the last figure was. <p>Harabec Woodwalker<br>Wanderer of 51 Seasons<br>Bears of Oboo</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utuonetar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuonetar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/12/02 4:58:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumdruid.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid Armor</span><hr size=1> +mana items give full mana but it takes that much longer to med to full <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarkomen42.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOmen42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardaholic</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/12/02 11:09:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumdruid.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid Armor</span><hr size=1> I realize that but someone was doing some test a while back that seemed to be showing that it didn't give the full mana.<br><br>Seems like it also said hp items weren't giving the full amount at level 1 either, not sure if they are or not. <p>Harabec Woodwalker<br>Wanderer of 51 Seasons<br>Bears of Oboo</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uartemecium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Artemecium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/13/02 3:35:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumdruid.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid Armor</span><hr size=1> They do give full amount, and it's VERY beneficial to have alot of hps items, it's like being buffed with skin like nature or whatnot.  Being level 1 and having the hps of a level 5 or higher is very nice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubeechwoodgrey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beechwoodgrey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/13/02 4:13:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumdruid.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid Armor</span><hr size=1> hmmm..interesting i did'nt get the same results when i twinked <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>When i started on another server at lev 3 someone approached me and offered me a glowing crock or some such thing..not really sure what but the damn thing hit for 23 to 27. That one item made one hell of a diff. ..just one item!!! (a lev 10 with a fs scimtar does about 11 or 12 hp of dmg tops)<br><br> Hara as far as mana items are you sure you are not thinking +wis.. they make very lil diff. at low levels i believe the conversion is (wis/5)+2)*lev according to EQ Druids so..a lev 1 with 200wis would have 42 mana.<br><br>A twink druid really is better off just meleeing everything in sight and reserving mana for heals alone, but there comes a point when your spells outdmg your melee than the mana is very importent..i much rather have tons of mana to finish a fight and live to med.<br><br>As an untwink you really do need to rely on your spells and melee once you reach lev 5 &lt;and hit orc hill&gt; as you are unlikely to have more than tattered leather till you start making enough money to support spell purchasing and gear..in otherwords you really can't afford to get beat on by a couple blue con mobs than have a third wander by. This is when stratey comes into play and the basics you'll be using to lev 60...course you'll prol be kiting just one till you get your first ae spell <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  not really sure if i would trust snare enough to even bother kiting more at a low level...anyone try it?<br><br>opps..gotta go feed the goats..later BWG<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarkomen42.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOmen42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardaholic</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/13/02 10:49:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumdruid.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid Armor</span><hr size=1> I know the difference between +wis and +mana =P<br><br>It's been a long time since I read the thread about it, I guess they've changed it and/or they guy's tests were wrong. <p>Harabec Woodwalker<br>Wanderer of 51 Seasons<br>Bears of Oboo</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td